Package sk.stu.fiit.logic

Class Employee

java.lang.Object
sk.stu.fiit.logic.Employee
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<Employee>
public class Employee
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<Employee>
This class represents a cleaner that works for the company. Also, use the EmploymentType, Schedule or Building classes to know even more details.

  • Constructor Details

    • Employee

      public Employee​(java.lang.String name, java.lang.String middlename, java.lang.String surname, java.lang.String email, java.lang.String phone_number, EmploymentType employmentType, double maxMonthHours, double[] maxDayHours, boolean[] available_standard, javax.swing.DefaultListModel<Building> restrict_buildings, javax.swing.DefaultListModel<java.lang.String> priority_city)
      Parameters:
      name - represents first name of the person
      middlename - represents second name of the person
      surname - represents last name of the person
      email - an actual contact email of the person
      phone_number - an actual contact cell number of the person
      employmentType - represents the type of the employment
      available_standard - represents typically available working days of the person available_act represents working days of the person during this week
      maxMonthHours - represents total month time that person can spent cleaning something currentMonthHours represents actual month time that person spent by cleaning something
      maxDayHours - represents total day time that person can spent cleaning something currentDayHours represents actual day time that person spent by cleaning something
      restrict_buildings - represents the black list of buildings, where an exact person can not clean
      priority_city - represents the number of cities, where an exact person can work schedule_list represents the schedule of the person for the current week
